cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.GR 

This paper is about object detection in remote sensing images, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel anchor-free detector, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also discusses the use of rotated anchors and NMS, which are related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with remote sensing images, which are often used in geographic information systems (GIS), making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible category.
